AI-Assisted Threat Modeling
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Implement AI-assisted threat modeling using local language models
Collect and process threat intelligence from open-source feeds
Generate custom detection rules based on threat analysis
Integrate threat models with Security Onion SIEM
Automate threat hunting workflows using Python
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of cybersecurity threats and attack vectors
Familiarity with Linux command line and Python programming
Knowledge of SIEM concepts and log analysis
Understanding of network security fundamentals
Lab Environment
Al Nafi provides pre-configured Linux-based cloud machines with all required tools pre-installed. Click Start Lab to access your environment. The system includes:

Security Onion SIEM platform
Ollama local AI model service
Python 3.8+ with required libraries
Suricata IDS/IPS
Elasticsearch and Kibana
